akespearesglobe.com/learn/research-and-collections/archive-collections/|title=Collections {{!}} Shakespeare&#039;s Globe|website=Shakespeare's Globe|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref>\n|-\n!Solos and chorus without harmony\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |2013\n|[[Tony Blair]]\n||[[Royal Court Theatre]]\n|Richard Bradberry; also starring [[Sasha Behar]], Aidan Casey, Ralf Togneri and [[Martin Turner (actor)|Martin Turner]].\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kristianbuus.photoshelter.com/image/I0000oMJq289.ig4|title=IMG_5954.jpg {{!}} Kristian Buus|website=kristianbuus.photoshelter.com|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref>\n|-\n![[Doctor Faustus (play)|Doctor Faustus]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |2007\n|Vega / Cornelius / Pope\n||[[Headlong (theatre company)|Headlong Theatre]]\n|[[Steve Marmion]]\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.phyllis.demon.co.uk/theatricalia/07class/class0009.htm|title=ROB WILTON THEATRICALIA Classic Play Programmes 2000 on|website=www.phyllis.demon.co.uk|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://actdrop.uk/news/news_listing?id=1496|title=The Wider Earth at the Natural History Museum {{!}} London theatre news {{!}} ActDrop|website=actdrop.uk|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Goold|first=Rupert|url=https://books.google.fr/books?id=dkcBylZuJwIC&q=andrew+bridgmont&dq=andrew+bridgmont&hl=fr&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjer76B4PToAhX9A2MBHauQDwA4FBDoAQgsMAA|title=Faustus|last2=Power|first2=Ben|date=2007|publisher=Nick Hern Books|isbn=978-1-85459-573-7|language=en}}</ref>\n|-\n![[Michael Morpurgo|The Mozart Question]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |2007 - 2009\n|Paolo Levi\n|[[Bristol Old Vic Theatre School|Bristol Old Vic Theatre]] & [[New End Theatre]], [[London]]\n|Julia MacShane\n|<ref>{{Cite news|last=Gardner|first=Lyn|url=https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2009/mar/30/mozart-question-review-new-end|title=Theatre review: The Mozart Question, New End, London|date=2009-03-29|work=The Guardian|access-date=2020-04-19|language