t0408403/|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n|-\n![[EastEnders]]\n|2004\n|George Wakefield\n|directed by John Greening.\n|<ref>{{Citation|title=Episode dated 23 February 2004|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0960310/|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n|-\n![[Murder Investigation Team (TV series)|M.I.T.: Murder Investigation Team]]\n|2003\n|DCI Bill Parkes\n|Season 1, Episode 6 directed by [[Susan Tully]].\n|<ref>{{Citation|title=Lambs to the Slaughter|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0638513/|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n|-\n![[Casualty (TV series)|Casualty]]\n|2002\n|Mr. Carter\n|Season 17, Episode 23 directed by Gwennan Sage.\n|<ref>{{Citation|title=Hitting Home: Part 1|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0537317/|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n|-\n![[The Bill]]\n|2002\n|Stan Cross\n|Season 18, Episode 48 directed by Jamie Payne.\n|<ref>{{Citation|title=037: One Last Day|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0524676/|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n|-\n![[Soldier Soldier]]\n|1994\n|SIB Officer\n|Season 4, Episode 11 directed by Michael Brayshaw.\n|<ref>{{Citation|title=Poles Apart|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0704378/|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n|-\n![[Between the Lines (TV series)|Between the Lines]]\n|1994\n|Publican (as Andrew Bridgemont)\n|Season 3, Episode 3 directed by Richard Standeven.\n|<ref>{{Citation|title=A Face in the Crowd|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0522381/|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n== Documentary ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"margin-right: 0;\"\n! scope=\"col\" |Title\n! scope=\"col\" |Year\n! scope=\"col\" |Role\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" |Notes\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" |{{Tooltip|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n![[Ahmed Salim#1001 Inventions|1001 Inventions and the Library of Secrets]]\n|2010\n|[[Abbas Ibn Firnas]]\n|Directed by '''Alan Deakins''' & produced by the British foundation [[1001 inventions|1001 Inventions]] aiming to promote the achievements of the [[Golden Age of Islam]].\n|<ref>{{Citation|title=1001 Inventions and the Library of Secrets|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1600740/|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n|-\n![[Peter Bridgmont#Honours|The Chrysalis Theatre Acting School]]\n|2009\n|Himself\n|Director by '''\u00c1lvaro Ramos'''.\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://medium.com/@portialeigh1/dynamic-spanish-actor-alvaro-ramos-makes-his-mark-across-several-mediums-c2392a7d74d1|title=Dynamic Spanish Actor Alvaro Ramos Makes his Mark Across Several Mediums|last=Leigh|first=Portia|date=2018-01-27|website=Medium|language=en|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=The Chrysalis Theatre Acting School|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1537921/|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n== Video Games ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"margin-right: 0;\"\n! scope=\"col\" |Title\n! scope=\"col\" |Year\n! scope=\"col\" |Role\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" |Notes\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" |{{Tooltip|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n![[Star Wars: The Old Republic]]\n|2011\n|Additional Voices\n|\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n== Books ==\nBridgmont is directly cited or mentioned in the following works (non-exhautive list):\n\n* ''Reading Shakespeare on Stage'' (1995) by\u00a0'''Herbert R. Coursen'''. [[University of Delaware Press]].<ref>{{Cite book|last=Coursen|first=Herbert R.|url=https://books.google.fr/books?id=LzWLwg7sxvYC&pg=PA269&dq=andrew+bridgmont&hl=fr&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj_z-OM4PToAhWPD2MBHWcXB1wQ6AEILDAA#v=onepage&q=andrew%20bridgmont&f=false|title=Reading Shakespeare on Stage|date=1995|publisher=University of Delaware Press|isbn=978-0-87413-538-1|language=en}}</ref>\n* ''Shakespeare Comes to Broadmoor: The Actors Are Come Hither: The Performance of Tragedy in a Secure Psychiatric Hospital'' (1992) by Murray Cox. [[Jessica Kingsley Publishers]].<ref>{{Cite book|last=Cox|first=Murray|url=https://books.google.fr/books?id=kySn8f0RBo8C&pg=PA273&dq=andrew+bridgmont&hl=fr&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj_z-OM4PToAhWPD2MBHWcXB1wQ6AEINjAB#v=onepage&q=andrew%20bridgmont&f=false|title=Shakespeare Comes to Broadmoor: The Actors are Come Hither : the Performance of Tragedy in a Secure Psychiatric Hospital|date=1992-01-01|publisher=Jessica Kingsley Publishers|isbn=978-1-85302-135-0|language=en}}</ref>\n* ''The Europa Directory of Literary Awards and Prizes'' (2015) by [[Susan Luckey|Susan Leckey]]. [[Routledge]].<ref>{{Cite book|last=Leckey|first=Susan|url=https://books.google.fr/books?id=2JhACwAAQBAJ&pg=PA139&dq=andrew+bridgmont&hl=fr&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj_z-OM4PToAhWPD2MBHWcXB1wQ6AEIQDAC#v=onepage&q=andrew%20bridgmont&f=false|title=The Europa Directory of Literary Awards and Prizes|date=2015-12-22|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1-135-35632-3|language=en}}</ref>\n* ''Staging Shakespeare at the New Globe'' (Early Modern Literature in History; 1999) by P. Kiernan. [[Palgrave Macmillan]].<ref>{{Cite book|last=Kiernan|first=P.|url=https://books.google.fr/books?id=PmuLDAAAQBAJ&pg=PA160&dq=andrew+bridgmont&hl=fr&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj_z-OM4PToAhWPD2MBHWcXB1wQ6AEISjAD#v=onepage&q=andrew%20bridgmont&f=false|title=Staging Shakespeare at the New Globe|date=1999-05-19|publisher=Springer|isbn=978-0-230-38015-8|language=en}}</ref>\n* ''Theatre at Stratford-upon-Avon: Volume 1'' (1994) by Michael Mullin. [[Greenwood Press]].<ref>{{Cite book|last=Mullin|first=Michael|url=https://books.google.fr/books?id=26odAQAAIAAJ&q=andrew+bridgmont&dq=andrew+bridgmont&hl=fr&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj_z-OM4PToAhWPD2MBHWcXB1wQ6AEIVTAE|title=Theatre at Stratford-upon-Avon: a catalogue-index to productions of the Royal Shakespeare Company, 1979-1993. First supplement|date=1994-01-01|publisher=Greenwood Press|isbn=978-0-313-25028-6|language=en}}</ref>\n* ''American Theatre, Volume 18'' (2001) by the [[Theatre Communications Group]].<ref>{{Cite book|last=|first=|url=https://books.google.fr/books?id=PhQrAQAAIAAJ&q=andrew+bridgmont&dq=andrew+bridgmont&hl=fr&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj_z-OM4PToAhWPD2MBHWcXB1wQ6AEIcDAH|title=American Theatre|date=2001|publisher=Theatre Communications Group|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=|language=en}}</ref>\n* ''Cahiers \u00c9lisab\u00e9thains'' (1989). [[Paul Val\u00e9ry University, Montpellier III|Paul Val\u00e9ry University Press]].<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.fr/books?id=LL5ZAAAAMAAJ&dq|title=Cahiers \u00c9lisab\u00e9thains|date=1989|publisher=Centre d'\u00e9tudes et de recherches \u00e9lisab\u00e9thaines de l'Universit\u00e9 Paul Val\u00e9ry|language=en}}</ref>\n* ''Plays and Players'' (1993). [[Hansom Books]].<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.fr/books?id=9MdBAQAAIAAJ&|title=Plays and Players|date=1993|publisher=Hansom Books|language=en}}</ref>\n* ''London Theatre Record'' (1990) and the ''Theatre Record, Volume 21'' (2001) by Ian Herbert. [[Theatre Record|Theatre Record Limited]].<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.fr/books?id=dS9aAAAAMAAJ&|title=London Theatre Record|date=1990|publisher=I. Herbert|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.fr/books?id=yYorAQAAIAAJ&|title=Theatre Record|date=2001|publisher=I. Herbert|language=en}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:English stage actors]]\n[[Category:English stage directors]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Andrew Bridgmont\n| other_names        = Andrew Bridgemont, Andrew Bridgemount\n| nationality        = British\n| alma mater         = [[Central Saint Martins]] & [[Waldorf education]]\n| occupation         = Actor\n| years_active       = 1994{{ndash}}present\n| home_town          = [[London]]\n| height             = 1.73 m\n| father             = [[Peter Bridgmont]]\n| website            = [https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1527333/ IMDB Page]\n}}\n'''Andrew Bridgmont''' is an English [[actor]], [[playwright]] and [[Stage Director|stage director]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://loveeast.london/people/eastlife/reflecting_on_darwin_with_andrew_bridgmont/|title=Reflecting on Darwin with actor Andrew Bridgmont|date=2018-11-30|website=LoveEast magazine|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref>, son of thespian and author [[Peter Bridgmont]] (January 1929 - 24 June 2019).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://goetheanum.co/fr/nouvelles/peter-bridgmont|title=Goetheanum {{!}} Peter Bridgmont, in memoriam|last=team|first=Maxime Le Roux, Nathan Querido, Das Goetheanum Wochenschrift|website=Goetheanum|language=fr|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref> He is primarily known<ref>{{Cite book|last=Morpurgo|first=Michael|url=https://books.google.fr/books?id=lP2mTwu7Jb0C&pg=PA90&lpg=PA90&dq=Andrew+Bridgmont+actor&source=bl&ots=5JuiNhz5my&sig=ACfU3U3n3vPFOg5L11hYlR91HeJ7J0wIlw&hl=fr&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjvu4DN6OjoAhVEhRoKHSwLDfA4FBDoATAGegQICxAx#v=onepage&q=Andrew%20Bridgmont%20actor&f=false|title=Morpurgo: War Plays|last2=Reade|first2=Simon|date=2012-09-24|publisher=Oberon Books|isbn=978-1-84943-541-3|language=en}}</ref> for his [[theatre]] work like at the [[Globe Theatre]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.shakespearesglobe.com/learn/research-and-collections/archive-collections/|title=Collections {{!}} Shakespeare&#039;s Globe|website=Shakespeare's Globe|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.grenfell.mun.ca/academics-and-research/Pages/school-of-fine-arts/programs/theatre/Guest-Artists.aspx|title=Guest Artists|website=www.grenfell.mun.ca|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.spotlight.com/interactive/cv/1/M1958.html|title=Spotlight: ANDREW BRIDGMONT|website=www.spotlight.com|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref> and appearing in such films as [[Matthew Vaughn]]'s [[Kingsman: The Secret Service|''Kingsman: The Secret Service'']] (2014), [[James Marsh (director)|James Marsh]]'s [[The Theory of Everything (2014 film)|''The Theory of Everything'']] (2014)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bibliotekalegionowo.pl/actor/andrew-bridgmont/|title=Andrew Bridgmont|website=POCZYTALNIA - nowe miejsce na twoje kulturalne eksploracje|language=pl-PL|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref> or [[TV-series|tv series]] like [[Penny Dreadful (TV series)|''Penny Dreadful'']] (2014-2016) or [[Grantchester (TV series)|Grandchester]]. Bridgmont was the winner of the [[International Playwriting Festival]] award<ref>{{Cite book|last=Leckey|first=Susan|url=https://books.google.fr/books?id=2JhACwAAQBAJ&pg=PA139&dq=andrew+bridgmont&hl=fr&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj_z-OM4PToAhWPD2MBHWcXB1wQ6AEIQDAC#v=onepage&q=andrew%20bridgmont&f=false|title=The Europa Directory of Literary Awards and Prizes|date=2015-12-22|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1-135-35632-3|language=en}}</ref> for ''Red on Black''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://damontproductions.blogspot.com/p/the-team.html|title=Tales from the Coast: Team|website=Tales from the Coast|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.warehousephoenix.co.uk/ipf86to02.html|title=internationalplaywritingfestival86to02|last=LTD|first=UKLIVE|website=www.warehousephoenix.co.uk|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Leckey|first=Susan|url=https://books.google.fr/books?id=2JhACwAAQBAJ&pg=PA139&lpg=PA139&dq=Red+on+Black+andrew+bridgmont&source=bl&ots=zmVlQ_GjNB&sig=ACfU3U28KraZJQBtMGybkzKJ8g3IDCEtyg&hl=fr&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwju6uS27ejoAhUHlhQKHaLjAUcQ6AEwB3oECAsQMg#v=onepage&q=Red%20on%20Black%20andrew%20bridgmont&f=false|title=The Europa Directory of Literary Awards and Prizes|date=2015-12-22|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1-135-35632-3|language=en}}</ref>\n== Education ==\nBridgmont initially enrolled in a [[foundation course]] at [[Central Saint Martins]] in [[painting]] (1980), studied at the [[Waldorf education]] (also known as '''Steiner education''', based on the [[educational philosophy]] of [[Rudolf Steiner]]) and went on to graduate with a [[Bachelor of Arts]] in [[Fine art|Fine Art]] in 1983 from the [[Royal Academy of Arts]] (RA). From there, he got involved with workshops at [[Ovalhouse]], formerly called '''Oval House Theatre''', an [[Off West End|Off-West End]] theatre in the [[London Borough of Lambeth]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://loveeast.london/people/eastlife/reflecting_on_darwin_with_andrew_bridgmont/|title=Reflecting on Darwin with actor Andrew Bridgmont|date=2018-11-30|website=LoveEast magazine|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref> Bridgmont is also a classically trained [[violinist]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=Gardner|first=Lyn|url=https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2009/mar/30/mozart-question-review-new-end|title=Theatre review: The Mozart Question, New End, London|date=2009-03-29|work=The Guardian|access-date=2020-04-19|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref>\n\n== Theatre ==\n\n=== Director ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"margin-right: 0;\"\n! scope=\"col\" |Title\n! scope=\"col\" |Year\n! scope=\"col\" |Role\n! scope=\"col\" |Director or Venue\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" |Notes\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" |{{Tooltip|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n!Summer of Love\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |2018\n|Director\n|[[St James's Theatre|St James Theatre]]\n|actor [[Thomas Brodie-Sangster]] playing Kenneth and [[Claire Porter]] as Kenneth\u2019s mum Rebecca; Damont Prods.\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ayoungertheatre.com/review-summer-of-love-st-james-theatre/|title=Review: Summer of Love, St. James Theatre|last=Jemma Anderson|date=2015-07-31|website=A Younger Theatre|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n|-\n!Summer of Love\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |2012\n|Director\n|[[King's Head Theatre]]\n|actor [[Thomas Brodie-Sangster]] playing Kenneth and [[Claire Porter]] as Kenneth\u2019s mum Rebecca; Damont Prods.\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ayoungertheatre.com/review-summer-of-love-st-james-theatre/|title=Review: Summer of Love, St. James Theatre|last=Jemma Anderson|date=2015-07-31|website=A Younger Theatre|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/westend/article/Thomas-Brodie-Sangster-to-Lead-THE-THREE-KINGS-at-St-James-Studio-20151116|title=Thomas Brodie Sangster to Lead THE THREE KINGS at St. James Stud